==English==
===Etymology===
Short form of '''[[pianoforte]]''', from Italian '''[[piano]]''' (soft) + '''[[forte]]''' (strong).  So named because older keyboard instruments, notably the [[harpsichord]] and the [[clavier]], could not produce varied volumes.  

===Noun===
'''piano''' (''plural'' '''[[pianos]]''')

#A keyboard musical instrument, usually ranging over seven octaves, with white and black keys, played by pressing these keys, causing [[hammer]]s to strike [[string]]s.<!-- encyclopedic; not necessary to the definition: Most white keys play one full step in pitch from each other, while the black ones play a half-step from the adjacent white. It may be played by a person or play itself.-->

====Usage note====
'''Piano''' is now the usual term for the musical instrument.  '''Pianoforte''' is old-fashioned.

